<doc>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAGS">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies configuration flags for HEVC video encoding.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAG_NONE">
    <summary>
      <para>None.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAG_DISABLE_LOOP_FILTER_ACROSS_SLICES">
    <summary>
      <para>Disables loop filtering across slices.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAG_ALLOW_REQUEST_INTRA_CONSTRAINED_SLICES">
    <summary>
      <para>Allows the usage of the intra constrained slices flag in picture control. This mode restricts the motion vector search range to the region box of the current slice, i.e. motion vectors outside the slice boundary can't be used.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAG_ENABLE_SAO_FILTER">
    <summary>
      <para>Enables the sample adaptive offset filter.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAG_ENABLE_LONG_TERM_REFERENCES">
    <summary>
      <para>Enables the usage of long term references in the picture reference management structures for HEVC.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAG_USE_ASYMETRIC_MOTION_PARTITION">
    <summary>
      <para>Enables asymetric motion partitioning.</para>
      <para>
        <b>Note</b> If <see cref="D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_SUPPORT_HEVC_FLAG_ASYMETRIC_MOTION_PARTITION_REQUIRED" /> was reported, this flag must be enabled.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAG_ENABLE_TRANSFORM_SKIPPING">
    <summary>
      <para>Enables transform skipping.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAGS.D3D12_VIDEO_ENCODER_CODEC_CONFIGURATION_HEVC_FLAG_USE_CONSTRAINED_INTRAPREDICTION">
    <summary>
      <para>Enables constrained intra prediction. This refers to constrained_intra_pred_flag in the PPS.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>